						               													<description>Read facial expression of characters, do they match with the story? Sometimes, it is not so easy to tell the delicate differences of emotions and sympathy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;ldquo;Can you hear me?&amp;rdquo; is an emotional training game that is developed to exercise social coping skills by empathizing with other people&amp;rsquo;s feelings.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Facial expression is an important element of reading emotions, and it is also a clue of mutual interaction that establishes the relationships with other people. Therefore, this game is designed to train general emotional system according to situations through storytelling, and to enhance the ability to build a social relation network.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It provides a training process to read emotions from character&amp;rsquo;s (four members of a family) facial expressions that fit the theme&amp;#10;&amp;#10;[Winning the game]&amp;#10;The player who collects most of the tokens by reading emotions well wins the game. Each player should listen well to other players&amp;rsquo; situation explanation, then look for the appropriate facial expression on the Emotion tiles that fits the story and place a token on that tile. It is not about one&amp;rsquo;s own feelings, but listening to other people's emotions and sympathizing and finding their faces on Emotion tiles accurately is what determines the victory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
